  "description": "The Architecture concentration introduces students to a broad understanding of concepts and methods for the planning and design of buildings and urban environments. It connects architectural education firmly to the humanities and provides greater awareness of historical, global, environmental, social and economic issues in the built environment. Students acquire skills in sketching, drafting, model-making, and digital rendering. NOTE: The Architecture concentration is open for current concentrators and students admitted Fall 2024. Starting Fall 2025, it will no longer be offered as an option for incoming first-year students.",
